she wouldn't tell me.

00:37.458 --> 00:40.375
Yeah. I forgot that
you used to do pageants.

00:40.458 --> 00:41.875
-That's right.
-(both laugh)

00:41.959 --> 00:43.000
All right. Let's, uh,

00:43.083 --> 00:44.458
let's get this dress
off of you.

00:44.542 --> 00:46.834
-Oh.
-Can I keep it?

00:46.917 --> 00:49.208
Uh, it's "May I keep it?"

00:49.291 --> 00:51.583
And the answer is no.

00:51.667 --> 00:54.250
Well, of course she can keep it.
She looks great in it.

00:54.333 --> 00:57.375
Who knows, Jen? You might have
a pageant star on your hands.

00:57.458 --> 00:58.667
(chuckles) We might.

00:58.750 --> 01:00.041
Yeah.

01:00.125 --> 01:02.333
She is beautiful,
but her real talent is math.

01:02.417 --> 01:03.458
Right, Lark?

01:03.542 --> 01:04.917
What's two plus two?

01:05.000 --> 01:07.333
Green.

01:07.417 --> 01:09.458
Spin around again. Show her.

01:11.125 --> 01:12.834
(Jen clears throat)

01:12.917 --> 01:15.166
Look what I had to peel off
our daughter.

01:15.250 --> 01:16.375
Oh.

01:16.458 --> 01:18.000
Did I miss Lark's
preschool prom?

01:18.083 --> 01:19.125
No.

01:19.208 --> 01:21.166
Colleen decided to dress up Lark

01:21.250 --> 01:23.250
in one of her
old pageant outfits.

01:23.333 --> 01:24.542
Freaked me out so much,

01:24.625 --> 01:26.041
I went and bought her a blazer

01:26.125 --> 01:27.875
-and some smart slacks.
-What's the big deal?

01:27.959 --> 01:30.875
Kids love playing dress-up,
and so do <i>some </i>adults.

01:30.959 --> 01:33.083
For the last time,
Iron Man and Wonder Woman

01:33.166 --> 01:34.709
are never having sex, okay?

01:34.792 --> 01:36.750
She's a natural-born superbeing,

01:36.834 --> 01:39.458
and he is a rich mortal
with some high-tech gadgets.

01:39.542 --> 01:41.291
Okay. The fact
that you even know that

01:41.375 --> 01:43.709
only makes this fantasy
more intense.

01:43.792 --> 01:46.125
It's just weird of Colleen
to be dressing her up

01:46.208 --> 01:48.375
in these girly costumes,
you know?

01:48.458 --> 01:50.208
I think I need
to say something to her.

01:50.291 --> 01:51.542
I really don't think
you should. All right?

01:51.625 --> 01:53.583
I mean, Matt and Colleen,
they're having trouble

01:53.667 --> 01:56.500
getting pregnant, and look,
this is making her happy.

01:56.583 --> 01:58.750
You know? Maybe you should
just let it go.

01:58.834 --> 02:00.750
(clicks tongue) Yeah.

02:00.834 --> 02:02.500
I guess you're right.

02:02.583 --> 02:05.083
Think of pimping out
our daughter as a mitzvah.

02:05.166 --> 02:08.250
Aw, you used a Jewish word.

02:08.333 --> 02:09.291
I did.

02:09.375 --> 02:11.000
All right, go get the costume.

02:12.083 --> 02:13.208
(grunts softly)

02:13.291 --> 02:14.500
(quietly):
Cool.

02:16.667 --> 02:18.667
(doorbell rings)

02:18.750 --> 02:20.417
-Hi!
-Hi.

02:20.500 --> 02:21.542
Oh...

02:21.625 --> 02:23.250
Uh, wow, Colleen.

02:23.333 --> 02:24.792
I wasn't expecting you.

02:24.875 --> 02:26.583
Well, I couldn't help but notice

02:26.667 --> 02:28.750
how much you loved
seeing Lark in my old dress.

02:28.834 --> 02:31.667
I mean, your face
was literally, like...

02:31.750 --> 02:34.542
(laughs):
It was. It was just literally
like that.

02:34.625 --> 02:36.208
I knew you caught pageant fever.

02:36.291 --> 02:38.583
So I brought over all these
outfits, so we can really see

02:38.667 --> 02:39.667
what we're working with.

02:39.750 --> 02:40.875
Mm.

02:40.959 --> 02:42.166
Now, I have one question.

02:42.917 --> 02:44.375
Can Lark twerk?

02:44.458 --> 02:45.792
-No.
-(groans)

02:45.875 --> 02:48.000
-But we tried, right?
-(both laugh)

02:48.083 --> 02:50.583
Well, if I can teach Joan
to twerk, I can teach anyone.

02:50.667 --> 02:51.792
Is Lark sleeping?

02:51.875 --> 02:53.041
Lark!

02:53.125 --> 02:54.750
Time to wake up!

02:56.083 --> 02:58.041
Okay. I'm practicing
my fake smile, right?

02:58.125 --> 02:59.333
So when Colleen comes out,

02:59.417 --> 03:01.625
even if Lark is spray-tanned,

03:01.709 --> 03:03.458
I'm just gonna go like this:

03:03.542 --> 03:06.083
"Look at you!"

03:06.166 --> 03:07.500
What do you think?

03:07.583 --> 03:09.333
Well, that's your brunch face.

03:09.417 --> 03:12.083
-I know!
-COLLEEN: Come on,
let's show Mommy.

03:12.166 --> 03:14.333
(chuckles) Wow!

03:14.417 --> 03:17.166
Look at you!

03:17.250 --> 03:20.375
I'm bringing sexy back.

03:21.458 --> 03:22.667
Doesn't she look amazing?

03:22.750 --> 03:24.166
If she got kidnapped right now,

03:24.250 --> 03:25.875
the press would have
a field day.

03:25.959 --> 03:28.083
Uh, excuse me,
did-did you put junk

03:28.166 --> 03:29.875
-in our daughter's trunk?
-Yeah.

03:29.959 --> 03:31.083
I had to pad her butt.

03:31.166 --> 03:33.333
The judges really respond
to curves.

03:33.417 --> 03:35.542
Sorry, uh, what judges?

03:35.625 --> 03:37.792
I signed Lark up
for her first pageant.

03:37.875 --> 03:39.792
Without asking me?

03:39.875 --> 03:42.208
Well, with "us."
She should've asked us, right?

03:42.291 --> 03:43.750
We can talk about that later.

03:43.834 --> 03:45.458
You guys, don't worry.
With my help,

03:45.542 --> 03:46.875
this little girl is gonna rise

03:46.959 --> 03:48.208
straight to the top.
Which, in this case,

03:48.291 --> 03:50.125
is the basement
of an airport Radisson.

03:50.208 --> 03:52.542
I'm sorry, no. I-I'm...
I have to put an end to this.

03:52.625 --> 03:55.041
-No...
-Enough. We're not entering
Lark into anything.

03:55.125 --> 03:56.166
But why not?

03:56.250 --> 03:57.500
Look how happy she is.

03:57.583 --> 03:58.625
GREG:
Yeah, but what does she know?

03:58.709 --> 04:00.166
She's chewing on her eyelash.

04:00.250 --> 04:01.500
COLLEEN:
Oh. Horse hair

04:01.583 --> 04:03.166
