08:14.458 --> 08:16.125
The other two,
you won't believe.

08:16.208 --> 08:19.375
Number one:
winter, 2004, Lillehammer.

08:19.458 --> 08:20.709
Where has Mom been?

08:20.792 --> 08:23.500
I mean, it's so unlike her
to just ignore brunch.

08:23.583 --> 08:26.125
Brussels sprouts were making
a real big noise on the scene.

08:26.208 --> 08:27.375
JOAN:
Matt!

08:27.458 --> 08:29.083
Matt, Matt, Matt!
I found it!

08:29.166 --> 08:32.000
My bike!
And it <i>was </i>on Craigslist!

08:32.083 --> 08:33.041
-Hey!
-A robber

08:33.125 --> 08:34.875
named Dale has it.

08:34.959 --> 08:36.250
I'm gonna go get him.

08:36.333 --> 08:38.417
Uh, Mom, you can't do that.

08:38.500 --> 08:40.709
No, don't worry.
I changed my identity.

08:40.792 --> 08:42.667
I told him my name
was Jen Short.

08:42.750 --> 08:44.208
Like my wife, Jen Short?

08:44.291 --> 08:46.792
I panicked. It was the first
name that I could think of.

08:46.875 --> 08:49.041
So, Dad is all right with you

08:49.125 --> 08:51.875
just meeting some stranger
off the Internet?

08:51.959 --> 08:53.500
Oh, no. He can't know.

08:53.583 --> 08:57.125
He told me to lock up the bike,
and I said, "You lock it up."

08:57.208 --> 08:59.959
And then I was on a bit of
a high for the rest of the day

09:00.041 --> 09:01.458
and I forgot all about it.

09:01.542 --> 09:03.917
Okay, Mom, you can't go
do this all by yourself.

09:04.000 --> 09:05.375
You don't know who this guy is.

09:05.458 --> 09:08.792
This Dale could be
some sort of weirdo

09:08.875 --> 09:11.250
who likes to sniff women's
bikes or something.

09:11.333 --> 09:13.625
Yeah, a real seat freak.
I know the type.

09:13.709 --> 09:15.834
Well, you know, bring him on.

09:15.917 --> 09:17.500
Because it's my bike
and I'm gonna be

09:17.583 --> 09:19.375
the only freak on that seat.

09:19.458 --> 09:20.709
Okay, well,
you're not going alone.

09:20.792 --> 09:22.291
No, we're gonna go with you.

09:22.375 --> 09:24.625
Oh. My boys.

09:24.709 --> 09:26.959
Road trip. Shotgun!

09:27.041 --> 09:28.500
Yay!

09:28.583 --> 09:30.875
Okay, here's the deal.

09:30.959 --> 09:34.542
First, I appeal to the robber's
sense of humanity.

09:34.625 --> 09:35.583
If that doesn't work,

09:35.667 --> 09:38.959
I've got a sock
filled with D-batteries.

09:39.959 --> 09:41.458
Hey, where's Tim?

09:43.625 --> 09:45.542
Ugh, we forgot Tim.

09:48.000 --> 09:51.709
So you guys didn't forget me,
you just stopped to get gas?

09:53.542 --> 09:54.834
Yeah, man.

09:54.917 --> 09:56.166
(Matt inhales sharply)

09:56.250 --> 09:57.333
So, what's the deal here?

09:57.417 --> 09:58.792
We gonna pay this guy or what?

09:58.875 --> 10:00.542
Pay for my own bike?

10:00.625 --> 10:03.667
No way, punk.
That's what I'm gonna call him.

10:03.750 --> 10:05.417
Do you think that's
rough enough?

10:05.500 --> 10:08.417
You know, or, I could joke
about his mother's weight,

10:08.500 --> 10:10.625
or I could say, you know,

10:10.709 --> 10:13.000
how many times
I've had my way with her.

10:16.166 --> 10:20.959
And here's a picture of me on my
bike when I ran the LA Marathon.

10:21.041 --> 10:22.500
Cute. Look,

10:22.583 --> 10:24.375
you're gonna need to give me
some better proof

10:24.458 --> 10:25.709
than some photos.

10:25.792 --> 10:27.375
The serial number, maybe?

10:27.458 --> 10:30.583
'Cause you can't just accuse me
of stealing your bike, Jen.

10:30.667 --> 10:32.500
Why you got the cute
little pink bike, man?

10:32.583 --> 10:34.417
Seem like more of
a sexy motorcycle guy.

10:34.500 --> 10:36.709
Thanks. I'm selling it
for a friend.

10:36.792 --> 10:39.875
Who? Your mother?
She has her own zip code.

10:39.959 --> 10:41.000
-Mm.
-Ooh, easy, Ma.

10:41.083 --> 10:42.417
His mom's easy.

10:42.500 --> 10:44.667
-What?
-I want my bike.

10:44.750 --> 10:47.250
Well, this bike... is 100 bucks.

10:47.333 --> 10:49.000
