Is the coast clear?

11:50.458 --> 11:52.208
Well, it depends on
what you want to do.

11:52.291 --> 11:55.792
(scoffs) I have a box
of Sophia's stuffed animals.

11:55.875 --> 11:57.875
Ooh, are you gonna put them
on the couch and watch a movie?

11:57.959 --> 12:00.166
No. I'm gonna give them
to Goodwill.

12:00.250 --> 12:01.792
She's letting you do that?

12:01.875 --> 12:04.041
Oh, no.
Babe, she has no idea.

12:04.125 --> 12:06.375
I have been running
an underground railroad

12:06.458 --> 12:08.250
out of her bedroom for months;
she hasn't even noticed.

12:08.333 --> 12:09.500
It's time to pull the trigger.

12:09.583 --> 12:11.542
-Yes. Tell you what.
-Yeah?

12:11.625 --> 12:13.667
-I'll cover you to the garage.
-Oh.

12:13.750 --> 12:15.959
Make sure the coast is clear.
(chuckles)

12:17.208 --> 12:18.291
Hey, Soph.

12:19.667 --> 12:22.166
What's going on down here?

12:22.917 --> 12:24.000
Nothing.

12:24.083 --> 12:25.458
Okay, what's in the box?

12:25.542 --> 12:26.583
Nothing.

12:29.542 --> 12:30.792
Nothing?

12:30.875 --> 12:34.333
Unicorns are mythical,
not invisible.

12:34.417 --> 12:37.125
Honey, you have thousands
of stuffed animals.

12:37.208 --> 12:38.583
How many could you need?

12:38.667 --> 12:40.542
How many children do you need?

12:40.625 --> 12:42.917
-Oh...
-Get rid of Tyler.
Then we'll talk.

12:43.000 --> 12:44.041
Sophia.

12:44.125 --> 12:46.917
Mom, you just don't see them
how I see them.

12:47.000 --> 12:50.625
They may just be toys to you,
but they're real to me.

12:50.709 --> 12:55.375
♪ <i>You say it's time</i>
