♪ <i>Yeah, he's always been there </i>♪

15:33.500 --> 15:36.583
♪ <i>By your side </i>♪

15:36.667 --> 15:38.875
-♪ <i>So I'll stop</i>
<i>from committing </i>♪
-Ow.

15:38.959 --> 15:42.250
♪ <i>This cutie-pie genocide </i>♪

15:42.333 --> 15:44.583
-♪ <i>Oh, you're right </i>♪
-♪ <i>We're right </i>♪

15:44.667 --> 15:46.041
-♪ <i>I can see </i>♪
-♪ <i>She can see </i>♪

15:46.125 --> 15:49.500
♪ <i>You're still making memories </i>♪

15:49.583 --> 15:52.792
♪ <i>You don't have</i>
<i>to say good-bye </i>♪

15:52.875 --> 15:55.875
♪ <i>Da-da, da-da-da-da </i>♪

15:55.959 --> 15:56.959
♪ <i>We don't have to say </i>♪

15:57.041 --> 16:01.542
♪ <i>Good-bye. </i>♪

16:02.750 --> 16:06.709
(cheering, laughter)

16:06.792 --> 16:10.166
♪ <i>So, now that</i>
<i>Sophia's had her turn </i>♪

16:10.250 --> 16:14.208
♪ <i>I'll let out the fire</i>
<i>that in me burns, ah. </i>♪

16:14.291 --> 16:17.458
Oh, yeah, that's nice, honey.
We're-we're done.

16:24.542 --> 16:27.083
(knock on door)

16:27.166 --> 16:29.542
What is it you two are doing
in here?

16:29.625 --> 16:33.709
Every day, Tank scratches
at the door.

16:33.792 --> 16:37.125
Is that jerky? Wait a minute.

16:37.208 --> 16:38.667
What have you done with Tank?

16:38.750 --> 16:39.959
Uh, Pop-Pop, calm down.

16:40.041 --> 16:41.667
We're just making beef jerky.

16:41.750 --> 16:42.959
It's our new side business.

16:43.041 --> 16:44.208
CLEMENTINE:
Yeah, and don't worry.

16:44.291 --> 16:46.959
No animals were harmed
in the making of this.

16:47.041 --> 16:49.375
-To be clear,
none of them lived.
-Hmm.

16:49.458 --> 16:53.709
We're calling it Pop Pop's
Old Fashioned Plan Beef.

16:53.792 --> 16:54.875
You recognize that guy?

16:54.959 --> 16:56.125
We wanted a handsome face.

16:56.208 --> 16:57.333
JOHN:
Oh, look at me.

16:57.417 --> 16:59.750
-I'm like Paul Newman.
-(both laugh)

16:59.834 --> 17:02.417
Or that Wendy's gal.
What's her name? Uh...

17:02.500 --> 17:04.208
You're famous, Pop-Pop.

17:04.291 --> 17:05.875
Yeah, well, I don't want
to be famous.

17:05.959 --> 17:09.125
I want to be rich.
Uh, so, what's my cut?

17:09.208 --> 17:11.291
-Your cut?
-Mm-hmm.

17:11.375 --> 17:13.375
Oh, we thought that you'd let
us use your face for free.

17:13.458 --> 17:15.166
Oh, no, well, you thought wrong.

17:15.250 --> 17:17.750
Hot looks cost money.

17:17.834 --> 17:20.041
I want 20% of your profits.

17:23.041 --> 17:25.750
So, we're drawing
salaries through our LLC,

17:25.834 --> 17:27.834
so technically,
we're not making a profit.

17:27.917 --> 17:28.917
Mm.

17:29.000 --> 17:31.417
Let's make it 30%.

17:31.500 --> 17:32.959
Partners?

17:33.041 --> 17:34.083
(chuckles)

17:37.625 --> 17:40.875
Mmm. Now I know
what kombucha is. (chuckles)

17:40.959 --> 17:44.291
All this time I thought
it was a Japanese puppet show.

17:44.375 --> 17:45.750
Uh, Pop-Pop,
what're you doing here?

17:45.834 --> 17:47.166
I'm here to move meat.

17:48.458 --> 17:52.792
Hey, there. Try Pop Pop's
Old Fashioned Plan Beef.

17:52.875 --> 17:54.625
Proven health benefits.

17:54.709 --> 17:56.041
Stimulates hair growth.

17:56.125 --> 17:58.000
Here, check out the results,
huh?

17:58.083 --> 18:00.792
Ma'am. Loosens you up
if you're clogged,

18:00.875 --> 18:03.500
-and it clogs you up
if you're loose.
-Ugh.

18:03.583 --> 18:05.709
Pop-Pop, you can't make promises
the beef can't keep.

18:05.792 --> 18:07.458
Yeah. That's why we like
to tell people

18:07.542 --> 18:09.959
that it's not that good for you,
but it tastes really good.

18:10.041 --> 18:11.208
And they respect that.

18:11.291 --> 18:12.667
Wh-What good is their respect?

18:12.750 --> 18:14.291
You want their money.

18:14.375 --> 18:16.667
Uh, we want a product
that is meaningful

18:16.750 --> 18:18.792
and creates a dialogue
with our fellow humans.

18:18.875 --> 18:21.083
You don't even sound
like a human.

18:21.166 --> 18:23.041
Hey, well,
why don't you just take a seat

18:23.125 --> 18:25.792
and be the face of the company?

18:25.875 --> 18:27.917
And let Clementine
and me take the lead.

18:30.333 --> 18:32.000
That coffee you made
this morning

18:32.083 --> 18:33.625
was seriously pretty good.

18:33.709 --> 18:34.875
It, like, woke me up.

18:34.959 --> 18:36.792
Aw. I love coffee.

18:36.875 --> 18:38.417
What the hell are you two doing?

18:38.500 --> 18:41.166
Oh, we're just enjoying
each other's company.

18:41.250 --> 18:42.834
You have to like
what you do, Pop-Pop,

18:42.917 --> 18:44.333
-otherwise,
it's not worth doing.
-Hmm.

18:44.417 --> 18:46.792
You're not even looking up
at your customers.

18:46.875 --> 18:48.125
That's right. They can tell

18:48.208 --> 18:49.667
that we're so confident
in our product,

18:49.750 --> 18:50.917
we don't need to pressure them.

18:51.000 --> 18:52.375
Well, that's crazy.

18:52.458 --> 18:54.500
Selling is all about
smoke and mirrors.

18:54.583 --> 18:57.291
If you're good,
you can sell sex to a nun.

18:57.375 --> 18:58.583
You just need a gimmick.

18:58.667 --> 19:00.250
You got to listen to me.

19:00.333 --> 19:01.875
Actually, we don't.

19:01.959 --> 19:04.417
As majority shareholders,
we control the vote.

19:04.500 --> 19:07.333
And we vote for you
to sit there and look good.

19:07.417 --> 19:12.166
Well, I'm sick of being treated
like a piece of meat.

19:12.250 --> 19:14.208
Beauty's a curse, Tank.

19:17.917 --> 19:19.500
Even though I'm scuba diving,

19:19.583 --> 19:22.458
you can put a rain cloud
above my head.

19:22.542 --> 19:24.208
That's my inner mood.

19:24.291 --> 19:28.458
Hey. Look what I stole
for us, Tanky.

19:28.542 --> 19:30.083
-(Tank barks)
-No, not now.

19:30.166 --> 19:32.750
My girl's got to turn a trick
for us first.

19:32.834 --> 19:35.667
(laughing):
There we go.

19:37.417 --> 19:38.875
There you go.

19:38.959 --> 19:40.041
Cute.

19:40.125 --> 19:42.625
She'll do anything
for this jerky.

19:42.709 --> 19:44.208
No, not me. The meat.

19:44.291 --> 19:46.583
Me, I'm-I'm her sweetheart.

19:46.667 --> 19:49.917
Maybe jerky isn't
the next cupcake.

19:50.000 --> 19:51.750
Maybe it's fruit leather.

19:51.834 --> 19:55.041
Or maybe it's just
more cupcakes.

19:55.125 --> 19:57.166
What about
a jerky-flavored cupcake?

19:57.250 --> 20:00.959
I'm cashing out my share.

20:02.333 --> 20:04.750
Good girl!

20:04.834 --> 20:07.583
Paw Paw's Old Fashioned
Plan Beef, the only treat

20:07.667 --> 20:09.917
you can share
with your best friend.

20:10.000 --> 20:12.583
-Tank. Speak! (laughs)
-(barks)

20:12.667 --> 20:14.208
Good for dogs,

20:14.291 --> 20:16.041
good for cats;
who cares about birds?

20:16.125 --> 20:17.792
Puts a shine on their coats,

20:17.875 --> 20:21.417
freshens their breath
and it's birth control.

20:21.500 --> 20:23.458
Are you selling our jerky
to dogs?

20:23.542 --> 20:25.458
Oh, we got a hit.

20:25.542 --> 20:26.542
And I need more product.

20:26.625 --> 20:28.333
How much you got left?
Thank you.

20:28.417 --> 20:29.709
Um, all of it.

20:29.792 --> 20:32.875
You should have listened
to the old man, I guess. Huh?

20:32.959 --> 20:34.500
Do you think you could
maybe cut us in?

20:34.583 --> 20:36.542
Sure, I'll give you a 20% stake.

20:36.625 --> 20:38.291
Is that net or gross?

20:38.375 --> 20:41.417
Well, if you can tell me the
difference, I'll give you 50%.

20:41.500 --> 20:43.792
20 it is.

20:44.709 --> 20:46.166
-Partners?
-Partners.

20:46.250 --> 20:47.333
-Partners.
-(chuckles)

20:47.417 --> 20:49.250
Now, get out of here.
You're bad for business.

20:49.333 --> 20:51.125
Beat it.

20:51.208 --> 20:54.125
-There you go.
-Thank you.

20:54.208 --> 20:56.250
Got two more left!

